  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      -  The aim of the present study is to examine the effectiveness of a short, highly
           structured parent based speech intervention program on speech development in very
           preterm children with a Speech Sound Disorder (SSD) at 2 years of age.

        -  The hypothesis of this study is that early intervention on speech development is
           effective in improving the speech development in preterm children with SSD at 2 years of
           age compared to a no treatment group (usual care at this age).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
